    "Silicon participants often came across as rational, utility-maximizing agents (e.g.",
    "\"Physical activity improves my health\"), possibly reflecting the dominance of theories of rational behaviour in their training data.",
    "However, human participants in our study did not display beliefs consistent with reasoned action theories (e.g.",
    "\"Physical activity does not bring any benefits for me\").",
    "While prevalent, these theories don't always align with real-world observations."
